dcterms:creator: B. D. Pena
D. T. Banuti
dcterms:description: A modified version of the Open AI Frozen Lake environment, which is a 2D pathfinding environment that includes hazards to the agent, along with 'slippery' tiles that introduce a random effect to agent actions within the environment.
dcterms:title: Open AI Frozen Lake Environment

dcterms:description: A novel environment designed for training models informed by depth-based visual information, allowing agents to navigate in a realistic manner without the need for translation into a grid world.
dcterms:title: Seeker Environment

dcterms:creator: A. I. Panov
K. S. Yakovlev
R. Suvorov
dcterms:description: A gridworld environment where the agent learns to navigate a matrix of cells, with each cell being either traversible or containing an obstacle, allowing for pathfinding in partially observable environments.
dcterms:title: Gridworld Environment
